servings: 2
---

1 olive oil
1 parsnip
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet Chopped Veggie Mix
1.25 cup boiling water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 bag baby spinach leaves
½ tbs white wine vinegar
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Israeli couscous

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Boil the kettle. Roughly chop parsnip.
• In a medium bowl, combine Louisiana spice blend, a small dollop of Greek-style yoghurt and a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken breast, season with salt and pepper and turn to coat.

• Place chicken on a lined oven tray. Place chopped veggie mix and parsnip on a second lined oven tray. Drizzle veggies with olive oil. Season, then toss to coat.
• Roast both trays until veggies are tender and chicken is cooked through, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, heat a medium saucepan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add Israeli couscous and toast, stirring occasionally, until golden and fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium. Add boiled water (1 1/4 cups for 2 people / 2 1/2 cups for 4 people) and chicken-style stock powder and simmer, stirring occasionally, until couscous is tender and water has been absorbed, 10-12 minutes.

• Add roasted veggies, baby spinach leaves and the white wine vinegar to cooked couscous. Toss to combine, then season.
• Slice Louisiana yoghurt chicken.
• Divide roast veggie Israeli couscous between bowls. Top with chicken.
• Serve with smokey aioli and remaining yoghurt.